# Ask Questions Rule

When working on this project, ALWAYS ask clarifying questions if:

1. Requirements are ambiguous or unclear
2. Multiple approaches are possible and trade-offs exist
3. You need information not provided in the conversation
4. The user's intent could be interpreted in different ways
5. You're about to make an assumption

## Examples of Good Questions

- "Should I include all environments (INT/STG/PRD) or just production?"
- "Do you want this change applied to the dashboard as well?"
- "Which deadline should I use for this item - 9/30/25 or 2/27/26?"

## Never Assume

- Status of applications without verification
- Deadlines or dates
- Team member assignments
- JIRA ticket numbers
